      <body>This updated patch causes keys that were grouped by to be part of a single array. So, for instance, the call:

@@@ ruby
  c = Account.count(1, :group =&gt; [:credit_limit, :firm_id])
  c #=&gt; [[[50, nil], 1], [[50, 1], 1], [[50, 6], 1], [[53, 9], 1], [[55, 6], 1], [[60, 2], 1]]
@@@

the &quot;50&quot; and &quot;nil&quot; would correspond to the :credit_limit and :firm_id.</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;
This updated patch causes keys that were grouped by to be part of a single array. So, for instance, the call:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;  c = Account.count(1, :group =&amp;gt; [:credit_limit, :firm_id])
  c #=&amp;gt; [[[50, nil], 1], [[50, 1], 1], [[50, 6], 1], [[53, 9], 1], [[55, 6], 1], [[60, 2], 1]]&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
the &quot;50&quot; and &quot;nil&quot; would correspond to the :credit_limit and :firm_id.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
